title: Tracy Rocker out at Georgia
text:
Tracy Rocker out at Georgia UGA has confirmed that Tracy Rocker is no longer with the Bulldog staff. Slot to Georgia Links 
Kirby Smart is dealing with his first assistant coaching vacancy as Georgia's head coach. 
247Sports has confirmed that defensive line coach Tracy Rocker is no longer on the Bulldogs' staff. Rocker also served as associate head coach. 
Rocker was entering his fourth season as an assistant at UGA, spending the first two under Mark Richt. During that time he was heavily involved in the recruitments of current Bulldog defensive linemen Trent Thompson, Jonathan Ledbetter, Julian Rochester, and Michail Carter, as well as 2017 offensive line signee Netori Johnson. 
Before his time at UGA, Rocker had spent three seasons with the Tennessee Titans as the defensive line coach. Prior to his stint in the NFL, he held the same position at Auburn, his alma mater. Other SEC stops for Rocker in his 23-year career as an assistant include Ole Miss and Arkansas. 
A two-time All-American on The Plains, Rocker won the Lombardi Award and the Outland Trophy in 1988. Author
